Certainly a hard-won lesson there. It’s a testament to the value of practical, hands-on assessment in truly gauging a candidate’s capabilities. I must admit, I’ve often fallen prey to the allure of the silver-tongued salesperson during interviews. It’s a perilous path.

On that note, I’d recommend augmenting your current process with something that ensures candidates are genuinely engaged and invested. Perhaps a brief, staged collaboration or a technical challenge that simulates their future role